entries.title: The West’s liberal establishment clings to D-Day’s legacy
entries.description: American and European leaders are using the occasion to voice new warnings for the future.

entries.title: Israel used U.S. munition in deadly strike on U.N. school, experts say
entries.description: Experts reviewed verified video from the scene and identified the weapons fragments as a U.S.-made small-diameter bomb.

entries.title: Why Netanyahu is facing an ultimatum
entries.description: How mounting pressure over Israel’s war in Gaza could break apart Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s coalition. And what it could mean for a ceasefire deal.

entries.title: Biden, world leaders and veterans mark D-Day’s 80th anniversary in France
entries.description: While the U.S. president’s speech was directed at a global audience, it came against the backdrop of a fierce domestic political battle with Donald Trump.

entries.title: Outages shroud Ukraine as Russian strikes on power plants take their toll
entries.description: After an attack over the weekend, the state electricity company, Ukrenergo, said electricity rationing would be needed throughout the country.

entries.title: Gaza aid pier suffered at least $22 million in damage, Pentagon assesses
entries.description: The U.S. military’s Gaza pier, which broke apart in rough seas late last month, is being fixed at an Israeli port and could be operational again within days.

entries.title: In photos: The last WWII veterans mark the 80th anniversary of D-Day
entries.description: Photographer Luke Sharrett takes us to Normandy as the world remembers World War II’s fallen soldiers.

entries.title: European Parliament elections 2024: How far right will the E.U. shift?
entries.description: From Thursday through Sunday, the E.U. is voting in the world’s largest election outside India. Here’s what to know.

entries.title: As Gaza cease-fire is debated, a vital aid route hangs in the balance
entries.description: The closure of the Rafah crossing has been catastrophic, aid groups say, limiting access to food and fuel as starvation spreads across Gaza.

entries.title: Border agents begin turning back migrants under new Biden restrictions
entries.description: Homeland Security launches President Biden’s new measures to block migrants’ access to the U.S. asylum system when illegal border crossings reach emergency levels.

entries.title: Israeli detention center faces legal challenge after ‘unimaginable abuses’
entries.description: Amid high-court scrutiny, hundreds of Gazan inmates were transferred out of Sde Teiman, a shadowy, military-run detention center in Israel’s southern desert.

entries.title: Israel to soon decide on Lebanon offensive as fighting with Hezbollah flares
entries.description: Three top Israeli officials warned an offensive at the Lebanon border could be imminent if the steady drumbeat of clashes with Hezbollah is not resolved.

entries.title: Here are the countries that recognize a Palestinian state
entries.description: Spain, Ireland, Norway and Slovenia are the latest to recognize a Palestinian state.

entries.title: India’s low-caste voters humbled its powerful prime minister
entries.description: Modi’s stunning setback in elections this week reflected the power of low-caste Hindus who rebelled against his ruling BJP.

entries.title: Gunman opens fire at U.S. Embassy in Lebanon and is shot by army
entries.description: The gunman, who has been hospitalized, was identified as a Syrian national. No motive for the attack has been reported yet.

entries.title: Biden, in France for D-Day anniversary, to stress contrast with Trump
entries.description: Biden’s D-Day visit will highlight the fight of democracy against authoritarianism, a reference to Donald Trump even if Biden does not explicitly name him.

entries.title: Tallest waterfall in China is fed by pipes, officials admit
entries.description: Yuntai Falls is considered China’s “tallest uninterrupted waterfall.” Officials admitted that its water is sourced from a pipe network during the drier months.

entries.title: King Charles III’s face arrives on Britain’s banknotes
entries.description: Most Britons have only ever had one monarch in their pockets.

entries.title: Here’s what to know about Modi and the Indian election
entries.description: Election results in India have not given Prime Minister Narendra Modi a predicted landslide majority. Here’s what to know about Modi and the election results so far.
